    About

    Description

    Jean-Michel Basquiat was an American artist who rose to success during the 1980s as part of the Neo-expressionism movement. Wikipedia
    Born: December 22, 1960, Brooklyn, New York, NY
    Died: August 12, 1988 (age 27 years), Great Jones Street, New York, NY
    Influenced by: Andy Warhol, Pablo Picasso, Cy Twombly, Robert Rauschenberg, Jean Dubuffet
    Periods: Contemporary art, Neo-expressionism, Primitivism
    Parents: Matilda Andrades, Gerard Basquiat
    Siblings: Jeanine Basquiat, Max Basquiat, Lisane Basquiat
